<section id="1project2">
    <div class="project2-main-container">
        <h1>Bhopal Mexico AI Based Road Inspection System</h1>
        <hr>
        <br>
        <div class="background">
            <div class="img-background">
                <img class="img-back" src="/images/61826915d734e7d4cc212ec6_the_use_of_artificial_intelligence.png">
            </div>
            <div class="content-background">
                <h3>Background</h3>
                <hr class="hr-1">
                <br>
                <p>Current road inspection practices are labor-intensive and time-consuming, with road surfaces deteriorating daily due to heavy traffic. This degradation not only affects driver comfort but also hampers economic efficiency. To ensure efficient road maintenance, municipalities conduct routine inspections. The project's goal is to leverage machine learning to study and analyze various road defects, automating the detection of abnormalities. Our objective is to design, construct, and evaluate an inspection system for this purpose, streamlining the process and enhancing road quality and safety.</p>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        <div class="problem">
            <div class="content-problem">
                <h3>The Problem</h3>
                <hr class="hr-1">
                <br>
            <p>Road inspections are currently time-consuming and labor-intensive, causing daily wear due to heavy traffic, impacting both driver comfort and economic efficiency. To address this, our project employs machine learning to detect road defects and abnormalities automatically. We'll design, construct, and test an inspection system equipped with cameras for data collection on roads with and without defects. The captured data will undergo analysis using Matlab's machine learning toolbox to train and test the network. Ultimately, the system will provide actionable recommendations for municipalities to rectify road defects. Our approach comprises three key tasks: data acquisition, data training/testing, and dashboard creation/testing, streamlining road maintenance and enhancing overall efficiency.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="img-problem">
                <img class="img-prob"src="/images/1_GM8W8pVmtLvTGyZSecsezw.png">
            </div>
            
        </div>
        <div class="goals">
            <div class="img-goal">
                <img class="img-g" src="/images/image_processing20220128-15506-hxjpcl.gif">
            </div>
            <div class="content-goal">
                <h3>The Project Goals</h3>
                <hr class="hr-1">
                <br>
                <p>This project's objective is to create, validate, and implement an inspection system utilizing machine learning for the detection of road abnormalities, defects, and damages. The system's primary aim is to streamline road inspections, reducing time and labor requirements. It will incorporate cameras to capture video streams from various roads, with data analysis carried out through the Matlab machine learning toolbox for network training and testing. The system will generate recommended actions for municipal authorities to rectify identified road issues. The project encompasses three core phases: data acquisition, data training/testing, and the development and testing of a user-friendly dashboard. Ultimately, this system will optimize road maintenance, enhance driver comfort, and boost economic efficiency while providing valuable insights into the root causes of road abnormalities in Indian urban and rural areas.</p>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        <div class="tech">

            <div class="content-tech">
                <h3>Technologies Used</h3>
                <hr class="hr-1">
                <br>
            <p>
                Our road inspection system employs advanced technology for automated detection of road defects and damages. Equipped with HD cameras, it captures live video streams from roads, enabling comprehensive data collection. Using the Matlab machine learning toolbox, the system analyzes this data, training and testing a network to accurately categorize road flaws. By harnessing machine learning and image processing, it detects issues like cracks, patching, rutting, and deformation. It enhances efficiency by offering recommended actions for municipalities to address these problems. The system features a user-friendly dashboard and graphical interface for real-time visualization and reporting. This project exemplifies how technology streamlines road inspections and enhances infrastructure maintenance.</p>
